Package: heatindexbr
Title: Heat Index Mapping for the Brazilian Semiarid Region
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Antônio", "Campos Neto",
           email = "antonio.camposneto9@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0009-0007-3844-3869"))
Description: Provides spatially interpolated Heat Index (Rothfusz 1990)
    climatology rasters for the Brazilian Semiarid region (1,477
    municipalities, Res. CONDEL/SUDENE 176/2024). The main product covers
    2000-2025 at ~1 km resolution across 288 combinations of month and
    local hour (12 months x 24 hours), interpolated using kriging with
    external drift (KDE) with covariate selection per combination via
    leave-one-out cross-validation. A municipal summary table and a
    population exposure dataset (IBGE Census 2000, 2010, 2022) are also
    provided. Data are hosted on Zenodo (doi:10.5281/zenodo.21049066)
    and downloaded on first use to a local cache. The 2025 synoptic
    product (four hours, annual means, doi:10.5281/zenodo.20942619)
    remains available via product = "synoptic_2025".
